1
00:00:01,100 --> 00:01:45,020
♪

2
00:01:49,010 --> 00:01:51,100
Human beings
going to the moon?

3
00:01:52,230 --> 00:01:54,060
It'll happen one day.

4
00:01:54,060 --> 00:01:56,080
-Mark my words, it will.
-Oh, I ate too much.

5
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:58,110
I though you were
going to be sick.

6
00:01:58,110 --> 00:01:59,220
Men will walk on the moon.

7
00:01:59,220 --> 00:02:01,160
What do you mean,
men on the moon?

8
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:04,290
I mean it will be a fact,
I am quite serious.

9
00:02:04,290 --> 00:02:07,060
You're quite delirious.

10
00:02:07,060 --> 00:02:08,200
Look, there
are people overseas

11
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:10,280
who have been
studying the idea.

12
00:02:10,280 --> 00:02:12,180
They will be constructing
a large cannon

13
00:02:12,180 --> 00:02:14,260
and actually shooting
men at the moon.

14
00:02:14,260 --> 00:02:19,020
♪

15
00:02:19,020 --> 00:02:21,070
Of course, the mathematics
involved in the calculations

16
00:02:21,070 --> 00:02:23,230
are extraordinarily complex.

17
00:02:23,230 --> 00:02:25,120
Why don't you calculate
something useful,

18
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:27,150
like how to make
food out of air?

19
00:02:27,150 --> 00:02:28,160
Huh?

20
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:30,070
Or maybe how to make
money grow on trees.

21
00:02:30,070 --> 00:02:31,230
(laughs)

22
00:02:31,230 --> 00:02:33,020
Huh?

23
00:02:33,020 --> 00:02:34,130
(sigh)

24
00:02:34,130 --> 00:02:36,290
♪

25
00:02:36,290 --> 00:02:39,080
Was that really true
what you were telling them?

26
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:40,130
(gasp)

27
00:02:40,130 --> 00:02:42,070
Kenshin, what are
you talking about?

28
00:02:42,070 --> 00:02:46,010
Not even little kids
believe a fairy tale like that.

29
00:02:46,010 --> 00:02:47,220
But I tell you
it is not a fairy tale,

30
00:02:47,220 --> 00:02:48,290
nothing like that.

31
00:02:48,290 --> 00:02:50,260
When science is much more
advanced than now,

32
00:02:50,260 --> 00:02:53,150
we'll definitely
be going to the moon.

33
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:56,050
I really envy the first
people who go up there.

34
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:59,000
♪

35
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:01,060
Thanks for being so polite.

36
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:04,110
Most people just laugh
at me and walk away.

37
00:03:04,110 --> 00:03:06,120
Hey, Daigoro, time to leave.

38
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:08,080
I'm coming right away, sensei.

39
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:11,180
Well, uh, goodbye.

40
00:03:11,180 --> 00:03:13,250
Now that young man's strange.

41
00:03:13,250 --> 00:03:16,270
I think going to the moon
is a romantic idea.

42
00:03:16,270 --> 00:03:18,260
You are kidding, right?

43
00:03:18,260 --> 00:03:21,270
Sano, you've got no
romance in your soul.

44
00:03:21,270 --> 00:03:23,040
He forgot his books.

45
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:24,200
He's not too organized.

46
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:27,110
I'll just take
them over to him.

47
00:03:27,110 --> 00:03:29,030
Whoa!

48
00:03:34,050 --> 00:03:36,080
(footsteps)

49
00:03:39,250 --> 00:03:42,040
What's wrong, sensei?

50
00:03:42,040 --> 00:03:44,170
Oh, oh, sensei!

51
00:03:45,170 --> 00:03:52,030
♪

52
00:03:52,030 --> 00:03:55,150
Hey, you forgot
your--what the...?

53
00:03:55,150 --> 00:03:57,240
Hey, what's this?

54
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:59,100
It's getting to the point
where decent people

55
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:02,060
can't even walk in the
streets of Tokyo anymore.

56
00:04:02,060 --> 00:04:04,240
♪

57
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,280
Move in!

58
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:09,270
♪

59
00:04:09,270 --> 00:04:12,060
(punching)

60
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:13,250
♪

61
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:15,180
Kori, cover those two there.

62
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:21,210
♪

63
00:04:21,210 --> 00:04:23,100
(punching)

64
00:04:23,100 --> 00:04:25,080
♪

65
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:27,240
Help, help, sensei!

66
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:30,110
Hey, Daigoro,
watch and learn.

67
00:04:30,110 --> 00:04:31,210
Ahh!

68
00:04:31,210 --> 00:04:36,000
♪

69
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Hey, are you two all right?

70
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,000
Yes, thanks to you.

71
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,180
That was our pleasure.

72
00:04:41,180 --> 00:04:45,020
I feel much safer with
her than I do with you.

73
00:04:45,020 --> 00:04:46,210
Whoa!

74
00:04:46,210 --> 00:04:47,150
Huh?

75
00:04:47,150 --> 00:04:53,020
♪

76
00:04:53,020 --> 00:04:54,230
(sword unsheathing)

77
00:04:54,230 --> 00:04:58,090
♪

78
00:04:58,090 --> 00:04:59,240
Sensei.

79
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:00,280
It's Tetsuma!

80
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:02,260
You know, a long
time ago I decided

81
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:07,190
that attacking my sensei
is just like attacking me.

82
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:09,170
But I fight back.

83
00:05:09,170 --> 00:05:11,070
Get out of here, now!

84
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:14,030
They always seem to run away

85
00:05:14,030 --> 00:05:16,000
just when it starts
to get interesting.

86
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:21,240
Sensei, are you sure
you're all right?

87
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:23,130
Yes, I'm just fine,

88
00:05:23,130 --> 00:05:26,060
because of these
good-hearted people here.

89
00:05:26,060 --> 00:05:28,230
I'm very grateful,
thank you, all.

90
00:05:28,230 --> 00:05:31,200
No thanks necessary,
it was good exercise.

91
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,260
Right?

92
00:05:32,260 --> 00:05:33,240
You're welcome.

93
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:38,000
Sensei Kaishu,
I've told you before,

94
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:40,240
you have to be more
careful when you go out.

95
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:42,150
Yes, you're right.

96
00:05:42,150 --> 00:05:44,090
If anything
happened to you now--

97
00:05:44,090 --> 00:05:46,190
I understand.

98
00:05:46,190 --> 00:05:48,190
I'll take you home now.

99
00:05:48,190 --> 00:05:51,120
Daigoro, listen,
if you are with the sensei,

100
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:54,060
you are supposed to provide
him with protection.

101
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:57,250
Um, um, I really am sorry.

102
00:05:57,250 --> 00:05:59,060
Tetsuma's right.

103
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:00,090
At this point,

104
00:06:00,090 --> 00:06:01,270
I think you're more
trouble than you're worth.

105
00:06:01,270 --> 00:06:04,140
But, sensei!

106
00:06:04,140 --> 00:06:06,230
♪

107
00:06:06,230 --> 00:06:09,110
If you're ever going to
grow up to lead this country,

108
00:06:09,110 --> 00:06:11,130
you'd better learn
to take care of yourself

109
00:06:11,130 --> 00:06:13,010
in addition to others.

110
00:06:13,010 --> 00:06:15,040
I really don't need
a pupil like you.

111
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:17,000
Hey, that's a
rotten thing to say.

112
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,100
You can't just
drop him like that.

113
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:21,070
You'll do well
to stay out of this.

114
00:06:21,070 --> 00:06:24,030
It's none of your business.

115
00:06:24,030 --> 00:06:26,210
You don't really think
this boy has any future

116
00:06:26,210 --> 00:06:28,230
if he just wastes
all of his time

117
00:06:28,230 --> 00:06:30,050
dreaming instead of doing.

118
00:06:30,050 --> 00:06:32,080
Well, with friends like that.

119
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:34,070
Sanosuke, I hate
to admit it,

120
00:06:34,070 --> 00:06:36,120
but you're absolutely
right this time.

121
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:38,050
And that's why I'm
going to teach this boy

122
00:06:38,050 --> 00:06:40,040
everything I possibly can.

123
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:43,220
He'll be a true swordsman
in the Kamiya Kasshin style.

124
00:06:43,220 --> 00:06:45,190
I admire your determination,

125
00:06:45,190 --> 00:06:48,260
but I think it's
a great waste of time.

126
00:06:48,260 --> 00:06:50,210
♪

127
00:06:50,210 --> 00:06:53,050
Daigoro, until you become
a decent swordsman,

128
00:06:53,050 --> 00:06:55,000
don't bother
coming to my home.

129
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,160
But sensei.

130
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:58,190
Come on, Tetsuma.

131
00:06:58,190 --> 00:07:03,160
Oh, by the way, young man,
what's your name?

132
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:06,030
Well, who are you?

133
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:09,130
Himura, Kenshin Himura.

134
00:07:09,130 --> 00:07:12,090
And as for me,
the name's Katsu.

135
00:07:12,090 --> 00:07:13,210
Kaishu Katsu.

136
00:07:13,210 --> 00:07:30,290
♪

137
00:07:30,290 --> 00:07:33,010
(crying)

138
00:07:33,010 --> 00:07:34,190
That's just about enough!

139
00:07:34,190 --> 00:07:37,110
He threw me out!

140
00:07:37,110 --> 00:07:38,280
You've got to pull
yourself together

141
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:40,210
and start acting like a man.

142
00:07:40,210 --> 00:07:42,030
If he had that
kind of self control

143
00:07:42,030 --> 00:07:43,120
I bet he
wouldn't have been

144
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:45,070
kicked out in
the first place.

145
00:07:45,070 --> 00:07:46,160
It's just so mean.

146
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:48,260
I don't care how great
a teacher he is,

147
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:49,250
you've got to have some

148
00:07:49,250 --> 00:07:51,240
responsibility
for your students.

149
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:53,060
Speaking of which,

150
00:07:53,060 --> 00:07:55,080
I find it incredibly
hard to believe

151
00:07:55,080 --> 00:07:58,170
that Mr. Katsu can really be
as cold-hearted as all that.

152
00:07:58,170 --> 00:08:01,020
Kaishu Katsu was a heavy
supporter of the Shogun,

153
00:08:01,020 --> 00:08:03,250
able to avoid
bloodshed many times.

154
00:08:03,250 --> 00:08:06,000
Hey, Kenshin, weren't his
plans what helped to save

155
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,100
Edo from the Satsuma
army's attack?

156
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,130
Yes.

157
00:08:09,130 --> 00:08:11,270
Even his fiercest enemies
admired and respected him

158
00:08:11,270 --> 00:08:15,080
for his diplomatic abilities.

159
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:17,090
When our envoy went
to the United States,

160
00:08:17,090 --> 00:08:19,160
Katsu was right
there with him.

161
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:21,250
He's a master
of political balance.

162
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:23,060
Well, he lost his balance

163
00:08:23,060 --> 00:08:25,120
when he threw Daigoro
into the street.

164
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:28,240
But we're gonna train him
and make him strong, right?

165
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:30,050
Well, I don't know.

166
00:08:30,050 --> 00:08:32,210
How about a little
positive attitude?

167
00:08:32,210 --> 00:08:34,010
You can only
accomplish something

168
00:08:34,010 --> 00:08:35,160
if you think you can do it.

169
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:36,180
Great idea!

170
00:08:36,180 --> 00:08:38,080
If I can learn to
take care of myself,

171
00:08:38,080 --> 00:08:40,090
he'll have to
respect me again.

172
00:08:40,090 --> 00:08:42,030
There, that's the spirit.

173
00:08:44,020 --> 00:08:46,270
(distant dogs barking)

174
00:08:46,270 --> 00:08:51,140
Ah, seito isu,
what is that?

175
00:08:51,140 --> 00:08:53,000
Well, it's a
form of science.

176
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,140
It's a field
of great study

177
00:08:54,140 --> 00:08:56,210
in most of
the Western countries.

178
00:08:56,210 --> 00:08:57,230
We're behind the times,

179
00:08:57,230 --> 00:08:59,190
and Sensu Katsu believes
this knowledge

180
00:08:59,190 --> 00:09:02,110
can really be of great
help to our country.

181
00:09:02,110 --> 00:09:04,060
-Hmm.
-What's the matter?

182
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:06,100
I just wish the sensei
could be as proud of me

183
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:07,230
as he is of Tetsuma.

184
00:09:07,230 --> 00:09:09,170
♪

185
00:09:09,170 --> 00:09:10,270
Tetsuma, isn't he
that stuck-up guy

186
00:09:10,270 --> 00:09:12,150
with the weird
straight sword?

187
00:09:12,150 --> 00:09:15,250
Yes, his sword is used for the
Western Kendo they call fencing.

188
00:09:15,250 --> 00:09:18,090
When he went to England
to study at the university,

189
00:09:18,090 --> 00:09:20,050
he learned to fence there too.

190
00:09:20,050 --> 00:09:21,100
He's very good at it.

191
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:22,180
And with his education,

192
00:09:22,180 --> 00:09:25,140
he's already promised
a high government office.

193
00:09:25,140 --> 00:09:27,070
His future is all set.

194
00:09:27,070 --> 00:09:28,140
♪

195
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:29,240
(sigh)

196
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:32,140
I don't think I'll
ever do that well.

197
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:33,110
But you know a lot more

198
00:09:33,110 --> 00:09:36,220
about this seito isu
thing, don't you?

199
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:38,040
I suppose so, why?

200
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:39,060
Don't you see?

201
00:09:39,060 --> 00:09:41,060
That means there's
something you're better at

202
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:43,060
than he is.

203
00:09:43,060 --> 00:09:45,200
So, if you really study
this seito stuff,

204
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:47,200
does that mean you
can go to the moon?

205
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:48,270
Sure, why not.

206
00:09:48,270 --> 00:09:50,290
Just look at this.

207
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:53,120
All right, listen carefully.

208
00:09:53,120 --> 00:09:54,220
Now, you take
a man and a dog

209
00:09:54,220 --> 00:09:56,140
and put them in this
giant cannon shell

210
00:09:56,140 --> 00:09:58,000
and fire it at the moon.

211
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:58,369
Wow!

212
00:09:58,369 --> 00:10:00,000
Yeah, yeah.

213
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,130
This is from a book by
a Frenchman named Jules Verne.

214
00:10:02,130 --> 00:10:03,230
It's titled something like,

215
00:10:03,230 --> 00:10:06,010
"A Trip To The Moon
and Back Again."

216
00:10:06,010 --> 00:10:09,110
♪

217
00:10:09,110 --> 00:10:11,090
Father, father!

218
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,220
What's all the noise?

219
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:16,190
It's too early for this.

220
00:10:16,190 --> 00:10:18,000
Hmm.

221
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,270
In case you
didn't notice, father,

222
00:10:19,270 --> 00:10:21,220
Daigoro didn't
come home last night.

223
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:23,040
Where did he go?

224
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:26,120
He will remain away until
he learns to use a sword.

225
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:29,050
It's not right for Daigoro
to learn sword fighting.

226
00:10:29,050 --> 00:10:30,280
You're the one who said
his greatest strength

227
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:32,130
was his intellect.

228
00:10:32,130 --> 00:10:34,120
And now you suddenly
decide it's all right

229
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:37,240
to abandon him in the streets,
defenseless and innocent?

230
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:40,100
Yes, well, whatever.

231
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:42,050
Shame on you.

232
00:10:42,050 --> 00:10:45,020
I'm going to find Daigoro
and bring him home.

233
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:46,070
Itsuko.

234
00:10:46,070 --> 00:10:47,290
I'm serious, father.

235
00:10:47,290 --> 00:10:50,030
Ah, well so am I.

236
00:10:50,030 --> 00:10:51,180
If you're not
going to obey me,

237
00:10:51,180 --> 00:10:53,100
you don't have to
come back either.

238
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:54,080
Hmm.

239
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:57,240
♪

240
00:10:57,240 --> 00:11:01,010
He doesn't even comprehend
the first thing about people.

241
00:11:01,010 --> 00:11:04,190
♪

242
00:11:04,190 --> 00:11:06,070
Good morning, Itsuko.

243
00:11:06,070 --> 00:11:07,270
Yes, morning.

244
00:11:07,270 --> 00:11:11,010
♪

245
00:11:11,010 --> 00:11:12,160
Hey, wait a minute.

246
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:13,280
Where are you going?

247
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:15,020
I told father

248
00:11:15,020 --> 00:11:18,060
I'm going to find Daigoro
and bring him home myself.

249
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:20,130
Tetsuma, I'm sorry.

250
00:11:20,130 --> 00:11:22,160
What are you
doing here so early?

251
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:24,110
I'm a little bit
worried about yesterday.

252
00:11:24,110 --> 00:11:26,220
I came to see
how the sensei is.

253
00:11:26,220 --> 00:11:29,040
As usual, stubborn
and pig-headed.

254
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:30,100
I see.

255
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:32,050
I have to go find Daigoro.

256
00:11:32,050 --> 00:11:35,130
Then, let me show
you just where he is.

257
00:11:35,130 --> 00:11:37,130
I know the dojo where
he's doing his training

258
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:40,080
and I'd be happy to take you.

259
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:41,220
Thanks so much.

260
00:11:41,220 --> 00:11:43,110
You're very thoughtful.

261
00:11:43,110 --> 00:11:46,030
(carriage wheels rumbling)

262
00:11:49,010 --> 00:11:51,220
(splashing)

263
00:12:02,010 --> 00:12:04,120
-Now we have balance.
-(yawning)

264
00:12:05,270 --> 00:12:08,040
Daigoro, starting today,
you are a student

265
00:12:08,040 --> 00:12:10,170
of Kendo Kamiya Kasshin.

266
00:12:10,170 --> 00:12:11,130
Starting today,

267
00:12:11,130 --> 00:12:13,210
you're the junior
pupil around here.

268
00:12:13,210 --> 00:12:15,260
We're gonna have fun now.

269
00:12:15,260 --> 00:12:17,240
(coughing)

270
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:20,120
Thanks so much.

271
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:23,020
So why don't you start
by cleaning up the dojo?

272
00:12:23,020 --> 00:12:24,140
(smack)

273
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:27,260
Ooh, ooh, oooh.

274
00:12:27,260 --> 00:12:29,260
I don't understand why I
still have to do this now!

275
00:12:29,260 --> 00:12:31,140
Don't give me
any complaints, Yoshi,

276
00:12:31,140 --> 00:12:33,270
it's an important
part of your training.

277
00:12:33,270 --> 00:12:36,030
Maybe he really
can learn something.

278
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:38,290
Stranger things have happened,
and with Kori training him,

279
00:12:38,290 --> 00:12:41,100
well, he could
surprise everyone.

280
00:12:41,100 --> 00:12:42,170
♪

281
00:12:42,170 --> 00:12:44,060
Aaah!

282
00:12:44,060 --> 00:12:46,150
(crashing)

283
00:12:46,150 --> 00:12:48,050
(neighing)

284
00:12:48,050 --> 00:12:49,210
Huh, whoa.

285
00:12:52,070 --> 00:12:53,070
This way.

286
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:56,130
Wha--Lady Itsuko.

287
00:12:56,130 --> 00:12:57,130
Huh?

288
00:12:57,130 --> 00:12:59,120
I'm glad that
you look so well.

289
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:01,060
Itsuko has come
to take Daigoro

290
00:13:01,060 --> 00:13:03,020
back to Sensei
Katsu's house.

291
00:13:03,020 --> 00:13:04,250
What, you mean
that stubborn old man

292
00:13:04,250 --> 00:13:06,070
came to his senses?

293
00:13:06,070 --> 00:13:07,190
We really don't
have to worry about

294
00:13:07,190 --> 00:13:09,120
what father
thinks right now.

295
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,160
Uh-oh.

296
00:13:10,160 --> 00:13:11,220
Yes, now come on.

297
00:13:11,220 --> 00:13:14,060
Aahh, hey, I said no.

298
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:15,100
Daigoro?

299
00:13:16,140 --> 00:13:18,130
I think Sensei Katsu
has good reasons

300
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:19,210
for me to learn the sword.

301
00:13:19,210 --> 00:13:21,120
I want to do it.

302
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:23,090
Everyone has
different strengths.

303
00:13:23,090 --> 00:13:24,260
Swords don't suit you.

304
00:13:24,260 --> 00:13:26,100
But studying does.

305
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:28,210
You're very good at it.

306
00:13:28,210 --> 00:13:30,020
Hmm.

307
00:13:30,020 --> 00:13:31,210
Listen, I'll talk
to my father.

308
00:13:33,190 --> 00:13:35,050
I won't go back.

309
00:13:35,050 --> 00:13:36,130
Look, Daigoro.

310
00:13:36,130 --> 00:13:37,250
You look, Itsuko.

311
00:13:37,250 --> 00:13:40,090
Daigoro is our student,
you just can't take him.

312
00:13:40,090 --> 00:13:42,120
He's here with us
because he wants to be here

313
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:43,130
and that's that.

314
00:13:43,130 --> 00:13:45,110
But he's our student,
our scholar.

315
00:13:45,110 --> 00:13:47,220
And your blockhead father
threw him out of the dojo,

316
00:13:47,220 --> 00:13:50,010
that was a bad
decision that he made.

317
00:13:50,010 --> 00:13:51,220
Why don't you
just stay out of it?

318
00:13:51,220 --> 00:13:53,120
Calm down, both of you!

319
00:13:53,120 --> 00:13:55,120
You stay out of this,
Yoshi, or else!

320
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:58,050
If he truly wants
to stay, let him stay.

321
00:13:58,050 --> 00:14:00,110
After all,
the decision is his.

322
00:14:00,110 --> 00:14:01,130
But, Tetsuma.

323
00:14:01,130 --> 00:14:03,050
As your father's
student for many years,

324
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,230
I think I understand.

325
00:14:04,230 --> 00:14:08,010
Kaishu Katsu does nothing
without a good reason.

326
00:14:08,010 --> 00:14:11,080
In this particular situation,
his thinking is obvious.

327
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,290
Daigoro has neither
the spirit nor the ability

328
00:14:13,290 --> 00:14:15,180
your father requires.

329
00:14:15,180 --> 00:14:17,140
What did you say?

330
00:14:17,140 --> 00:14:18,150
It's better for him

331
00:14:18,150 --> 00:14:20,180
if his skills
are never tested.

332
00:14:20,180 --> 00:14:25,220
For him, to cross
blades in this dojo--

333
00:14:25,220 --> 00:14:29,100
I'm sorry, but I don't think
Daigoro will gain anything

334
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:32,010
from taking weapons
training here.

335
00:14:32,010 --> 00:14:34,100
Then again, maybe it's
a perfect place for him.

336
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:36,050
No pressure
to achieve anything,

337
00:14:36,050 --> 00:14:37,250
a woman for his teacher.

338
00:14:37,250 --> 00:14:40,000
(growling)

339
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,120
♪

340
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:43,070
I think that maybe you
need an introduction

341
00:14:43,070 --> 00:14:45,120
to the power
of Kamiya Kasshin.

342
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:46,250
Prepare yourself.

343
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:49,250
I learned my style
from masters of the blade.

344
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:51,070
It's called fencing

345
00:14:51,070 --> 00:14:54,060
and it was taught
to me in the West.

346
00:14:54,060 --> 00:14:55,290
Tetsuma, don't do this.

347
00:14:55,290 --> 00:14:58,010
Not to worry, Itsuko,

348
00:14:58,010 --> 00:14:59,130
I'm just going to
show her what it's like

349
00:14:59,130 --> 00:15:01,180
when a girl plays along
with the big boys.

350
00:15:01,180 --> 00:15:02,200
No, Tetsuma.

351
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:04,040
Step aside, please.

352
00:15:04,040 --> 00:15:08,100
♪

353
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:09,190
Now prepare yourself.

354
00:15:09,190 --> 00:15:11,090
♪

355
00:15:11,090 --> 00:15:13,280
It looks like
he knows his blade.

356
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:15,180
I'll never understand
why you people

357
00:15:15,180 --> 00:15:18,170
are still using sticks
in this day and age.

358
00:15:18,170 --> 00:15:20,140
See what a stick can do!

359
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:23,030
Aaahh!

360
00:15:23,030 --> 00:15:25,090
(gasping)

361
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:27,050
Ughhhh.

362
00:15:29,190 --> 00:15:30,260
Please don't fight

363
00:15:30,260 --> 00:15:34,190
'cause someone
might really get hurt.

364
00:15:34,190 --> 00:15:36,080
I'm so sorry, Kenshin.

365
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:37,040
Uhh.

366
00:15:40,050 --> 00:15:42,210
I have some important
business to take care of.

367
00:15:42,210 --> 00:15:44,240
Look, Itsuko,
I have to leave now,

368
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:46,190
so please promise
me you'll be careful

369
00:15:46,190 --> 00:15:48,020
on your way home.

370
00:15:48,020 --> 00:15:51,030
(footsteps)

371
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:57,150
I'm quite
serious about this.

372
00:15:57,150 --> 00:15:59,260
I'm going to stay and
study with Sensei Kori.

373
00:15:59,260 --> 00:16:02,000
Please tell Sensei Katsu.

374
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,110
I understand.

375
00:16:03,110 --> 00:16:04,230
If that's really
your decision,

376
00:16:04,230 --> 00:16:07,020
then I won't say
anything more to my father.

377
00:16:07,020 --> 00:16:09,140
But I want you to know,
I'll be staying here too.

378
00:16:09,140 --> 00:16:11,190
Wait a minute,
you'll be doing what?

379
00:16:11,190 --> 00:16:12,230
I'll be staying right here

380
00:16:12,230 --> 00:16:14,140
until Daigoro
is sufficiently trained

381
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:16,160
to satisfy my father.

382
00:16:16,160 --> 00:16:19,070
(gong ringing)

383
00:16:19,070 --> 00:16:21,240
(crow cawing)

384
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:24,100
♪

385
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:26,260
What do you think
you're doing, Itsuko?

386
00:16:26,260 --> 00:16:27,220
What do you mean?

387
00:16:27,220 --> 00:16:29,190
I'm cooking dinner
for the dojo.

388
00:16:29,190 --> 00:16:31,210
But you can't do that?

389
00:16:31,210 --> 00:16:33,110
I've just got
to do something.

390
00:16:33,110 --> 00:16:35,270
♪

391
00:16:35,270 --> 00:16:38,220
And I happen to be
very good at cooking.

392
00:16:38,220 --> 00:16:39,260
Is that all right?

393
00:16:39,260 --> 00:16:41,070
Well, you see,
it's like this--

394
00:16:41,070 --> 00:16:42,240
Hey, it's good!

395
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:44,120
What, it tastes good?

396
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:44,455
Ooh!

397
00:16:44,455 --> 00:16:47,140
♪

398
00:16:47,140 --> 00:16:49,000
You're right, Yoshi,
it's really good!

399
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,200
(gulping)

400
00:16:50,200 --> 00:16:51,290
Better than Kori's!

401
00:16:51,290 --> 00:16:53,240
What do you mean
better than mine?

402
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:56,130
Dirt is better
than your cooking.

403
00:16:56,130 --> 00:16:59,080
You must be getting tired.

404
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:02,240
I had no idea what a task
master Sensei Kori can be.

405
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:04,130
(laughing)

406
00:17:04,130 --> 00:17:07,140
Yes, she even finds work
for me if I don't hide.

407
00:17:07,140 --> 00:17:08,250
By the way,
I'm really impressed

408
00:17:08,250 --> 00:17:11,240
by your dedication of study.

409
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:13,290
Sometimes I think
that's my only strength.

410
00:17:13,290 --> 00:17:21,100
♪

411
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:23,050
You know, Kenshin,
I can't help thinking

412
00:17:23,050 --> 00:17:25,150
that a guy like Tetsuma
is absolutely perfect

413
00:17:25,150 --> 00:17:27,100
for someone like Lady Itsuko.

414
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:34,000
♪

415
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,010
No, I don't think I agree.

416
00:17:36,010 --> 00:17:37,250
(sigh)

417
00:17:37,250 --> 00:17:39,190
Well, I know the truth.

418
00:17:39,190 --> 00:17:42,000
I've seen people like
Tetsuma all my life.

419
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,170
They're the ones
who never seem to lose.

420
00:17:44,170 --> 00:17:47,180
Doesn't seem fair,
but that's real life.

421
00:17:47,180 --> 00:17:49,160
But Itsuko
disobeyed her father,

422
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:51,020
left her home,
and traveled here

423
00:17:51,020 --> 00:17:52,210
because she was
worried about you.

424
00:17:52,210 --> 00:17:54,100
She really cares for you.

425
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:55,140
(gasp)

426
00:17:55,140 --> 00:17:59,070
♪

427
00:17:59,070 --> 00:18:02,000
Everyone, dinner is ready.

428
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,270
Thank you, we'll
be right there.

429
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:09,100
Itsuko, that was great.

430
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:12,170
Where are you going,

431
00:18:12,170 --> 00:18:14,140
you got an after
dinner appointment?

432
00:18:14,140 --> 00:18:18,120
I need to tell Kaishu Katsu
where his daughter is.

433
00:18:18,120 --> 00:18:20,030
Going to my father?

434
00:18:20,030 --> 00:18:22,010
Kenshin, please
don't do that.

435
00:18:22,010 --> 00:18:23,160
I don't think
he's even worried.

436
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:25,110
-More please!
-Me too!

437
00:18:25,110 --> 00:18:26,200
Huh?

438
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,270
(crickets chirping)

439
00:18:28,270 --> 00:18:31,070
(water gurgling)

440
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:01,270
Oh, it's you.

441
00:19:01,270 --> 00:19:05,000
Sorry to drop by
without notice, sensei.

442
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,050
Not to worry.

443
00:19:06,050 --> 00:19:07,110
I'm the only one here

444
00:19:07,110 --> 00:19:09,170
in this big
empty house, anyway.

445
00:19:09,170 --> 00:19:11,020
I just came by
to let you know

446
00:19:11,020 --> 00:19:12,180
that your daughter
is all right

447
00:19:12,180 --> 00:19:15,170
and she's staying at
the Kamiya dojo with Daigoro.

448
00:19:15,170 --> 00:19:18,050
Thank you for taking
care of them both.

449
00:19:18,050 --> 00:19:19,160
She's such a rebel.

450
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:22,100
I hope she's not
giving you any trouble.

451
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:23,140
Not at all.

452
00:19:23,140 --> 00:19:25,220
She's a wonderful cook
and a warm spirit.

453
00:19:25,220 --> 00:19:27,160
It's good to have her there.

454
00:19:27,160 --> 00:19:28,230
Good news.

455
00:19:28,230 --> 00:19:30,210
Always pleasant to hear.

456
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:33,220
(water gurgling)

457
00:19:33,220 --> 00:19:45,040
♪

458
00:19:45,040 --> 00:19:47,220
It's so very quiet.

459
00:19:47,220 --> 00:19:50,270
Makes me think of things
I never got to do.

460
00:19:50,270 --> 00:19:52,250
Ever think of those things?

461
00:19:52,250 --> 00:19:53,240
Sure I do.

462
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:57,040
You know, every once in
a while, everyone does.

463
00:19:57,040 --> 00:19:58,130
In the old days,

464
00:19:58,130 --> 00:20:02,120
I could never imagine having
an evening visit like this.

465
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:04,260
I was quite famous, you know.

466
00:20:04,260 --> 00:20:06,290
A lot of men
wanted to kill me.

467
00:20:06,290 --> 00:20:10,120
And fortunately
for me, they missed.

468
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:36,050
♪

469
00:20:36,050 --> 00:20:38,240
There was such
fire in our hearts,

470
00:20:38,240 --> 00:20:41,280
everyone staking his
life for his beliefs.

471
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:43,150
Bring down the Shogun.

472
00:20:43,150 --> 00:20:45,030
Save the Shogun.

473
00:20:45,030 --> 00:20:46,110
Hope in the country.

474
00:20:46,110 --> 00:20:47,270
Keep the foreigners out.

475
00:20:47,270 --> 00:20:51,060
Ah, we lived
one day at a time.

476
00:20:51,060 --> 00:20:53,210
Now I look to the future.

477
00:20:53,210 --> 00:20:56,200
My time, my kind, are over.

478
00:20:56,200 --> 00:20:58,180
It's up to
the younger generation

479
00:20:58,180 --> 00:21:00,170
to fix our mistakes.

480
00:21:00,170 --> 00:21:04,250
Or to make their own.

481
00:21:04,250 --> 00:21:06,160
Mr. Katsu.

482
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:09,120
Sorry if I tend
to ramble, young man.

483
00:21:09,120 --> 00:21:11,110
I'm just an
old man reminiscing.

484
00:21:11,110 --> 00:21:13,100
You should just
forget about it.

485
00:21:13,100 --> 00:21:15,230
Mr. Katsu, I don't
think you really believe

486
00:21:15,230 --> 00:21:18,060
your work is quite done.

487
00:21:18,060 --> 00:21:21,060
Well, you're wrong.

488
00:21:21,060 --> 00:21:23,060
Hmm.

489
00:21:23,060 --> 00:21:27,150
Please take care of my Itsuko,
and Daigoro as well.

490
00:21:27,150 --> 00:21:29,180
Wont you, Mr. Battousai?

491
00:21:29,180 --> 00:21:32,140
♪

492
00:21:32,140 --> 00:21:34,070
Sorry, my mistake,

493
00:21:34,070 --> 00:21:36,140
you're called Kenshin
Himura these days.

494
00:21:36,140 --> 00:21:38,170
♪

495
00:21:38,170 --> 00:21:39,230
That's right.

496
00:21:39,230 --> 00:21:42,120
And don't worry,
I will take care of them.

497
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:44,130
Mmm.

498
00:21:44,130 --> 00:21:55,160
♪

499
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:57,200
What is Kaishu
Katsu working on?

500
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:59,040
What's his plan?

501
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:00,260
And is he pushing
his daughter and student

502
00:22:00,260 --> 00:22:04,190
out of danger, or into it?

503
00:22:04,190 --> 00:22:06,080
(footsteps running)

504
00:22:06,080 --> 00:22:16,290
♪

505
00:22:16,290 --> 00:22:18,170
(footsteps running)

506
00:22:18,170 --> 00:22:23,070
♪

507
00:22:23,070 --> 00:22:26,100
You might as well just
come on out and say hello.

508
00:22:26,100 --> 00:22:30,260
♪

509
00:22:30,260 --> 00:22:32,260
Didn't I see you yesterday?

510
00:22:32,260 --> 00:22:34,140
Don't get involved.

511
00:22:34,140 --> 00:22:37,080
You stay away
from Kaishu Katsu.

512
00:22:37,080 --> 00:22:46,240
♪

513
00:22:49,120 --> 00:25:15,230
♪

